<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: More customization options Classic Shell]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7705&amp;p=33143#p33143"><![CDATA[
1. you can change this, but you have to modify the .skin file (its a bit advanced but its there)<br />2. again something you can already do with a skin<br />3. I do actually like this idea. (though IVO has the final say)<br />4. custom buttons are really all you need. (though an easy way to browse the ones submitted online would be nice)<br />5. you can already add custom items to the left, or right, though its not drag/drop (you have to add them in the Classic start menu settings dialog)<br />6. an option to input commands into the searchbox might be cool (and basic stuff like a calculator, or commands like 'google &quot;Insert text&quot; to open up a google search) but is more in-line with what cortana does.<br />7. skins control everything about the submenu, and an option can already be implemented via skin options if the user wished (or hardcoded)<br />8.?<br />9.  the 'all programs' &amp; 'Apps' subs menu are already sorted alphabetically<br />10. ?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=62">Jcee</a> — Sun Jun 25, 2017 11:55 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
